== Roast the Veggies ==

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat
oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Dice @sweet potato{1} into ½-inch pieces. Trim and quarter @button mushrooms{4%ounce}.
Core, deseed, and dice @bell pepper{1} into ½-inch pieces. Zest and quarter @lime{1}.
Trim and very thinly slice @radishes{2} into rounds.

In a #medium bowl{}, toss sweet potato and mushrooms with half the @hoisin sauce{2%tablespoon}
(you'll use the rest later), a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon}, @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Spread out on one side of a #baking sheet{}. (For 4 servings, spread sweet
potatoes and mushrooms out across entire sheet.)

Toss bell pepper on empty side with a drizzle of oil; season with salt and pepper.
(For 4, add bell peppers to a second #sheet{}; roast sweet potatoes and
mushrooms on top rack and bell peppers on middle rack.)

Roast on top rack for ~{15%minutes} (the veggies will finish cooking in step 5).

== Pickled Radishes ==

While veggies roast, in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine juice from half the
lime, @sugar{½%teaspoon} (1 tsp for 4 servings), a splash of @water{some}, and a
pinch of salt and pepper. Stir in sliced radishes. Cover #bowl{} with #plastic wrap{}.

Microwave for ~{30%seconds}.

Remove plastic wrap; stir and set aside to pickle.

== Creamy Sriracha Sauce ==

In a second #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @sour cream{2%tablespoon},
and as much @sriracha{1%teaspoon} as you like.

> Start with half the sriracha, then taste and add more from there if you like things spicy.

== Glaze and Finish Roasting ==

Once veggies have roasted ~{15%minutes}, remove sheet from oven. (For 4 servings,
remove sheet with sweet potatoes and mushrooms; leave bell peppers in the oven.)

Using a #spatula{}, toss sweet potato and mushrooms with a pinch of lime zest,
remaining hoisin, and half the @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon} (save the rest for serving).

Return to top rack until veggies are tender and glaze is tacky, ~{5-8%minutes} more.

== Warm the Tortillas and Assemble ==

Meanwhile, wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until
warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates; fill with roasted veggie mixture. Top with
@crispy fried onions{1}, pickled radishes (draining first), and remaining
@sesame seeds{1%tablespoon}. Drizzle with as much creamy sriracha sauce as you like.
Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.